
(A/N- sorry it's super short!)
She stood at her mothers gave, looking down at the head stone. Her boyfriend stood a few feet behind Robin. Giving her some room to think and be alone. It seems like the crash was months ago, Robin had learned so much in that short time.
The sun shown through a patch of clouds. Birds chirp to another in the trees. Robin looked at the flowers in her hand before setting them next to her mothers grave.
"I love you mom. I want you to know that I will always miss you, Sara, your sister, has been more than good to me." She said as glanced down one last time before walking to Thomas. He put this arm around her as they walked to the car.
"She would be proud of you. You know that right?" He asked her as they buckled up.
"Yea." She replied as they drove back to California.